{
  "stem": "6195.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was related sort of in that business with somebody else, too.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we were well off.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we didn't know, like, we children did know, what our parents had or didn't have.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "To them, we were brought up to be like all other children around us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Which, in a way, was good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because when you go to school, you're mixed with rich children and poor children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In the building-- which belonged to my parents, where I was born and I grew up-- there were poor and rich.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So because that was my parents' thinking, because we didn't know in which way we are different to those children.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were just one of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At school, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were Christians, as well.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, with the Christians in the building and with the girls at school, we had a very good to relationship, so much so that when my father used to go to shul, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and they were throwing stones after Jews, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the boys from the non-Jewish families in our building were standing there, don't throw a stone at Mr.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Florenz.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a reason behind it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were poor, very poor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They couldn't pay the rent.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my father would never sort of put them out into the street.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He said if they could, they would pay.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He is-- it was in, in the family, like my grandfather, too.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were a very philanthropic family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They belonged to the known philanthropic societies.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We had, one a year, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we-- not-- when I say we, I mean my parents and my grandfathers, my grandparents-- invite, I can't be precise, whether it was 200 people or 300 people.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
